<br>
The spell Retribution does damage to the mob and Mark of Karm heals a small amount per main hand hit. My theory is that Mark of Retribution adds a small amount of damage to main hand attacks, kinda like an inverted damage shield. I can't think of any way to test that theory though without a LOT of data. Maybe when I'm bored I'll log all my attacks with my warrior and cast MoR on all the mobs he fights for a week. When I cast it stuff dies faster. That's good enough for me. <p><DIV align=center><A href=http://www.kyid.net target=top><FONT face=Tempus Sans ITC alias color=#33cccc ><img src=http://ldnews.kyid.net/images/members/derenath.jpg></A><BR>Derenath 60 Dwarven Cleric<BR>Theek 51 Ogre Warrior<BR>Lumiere Divine</DIV></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uadonborealis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adon Borealis</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_yellowspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tunare's n00b</span><br>  Posts: 431<br> <font color=#333333>(12/12/01 11:19:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=64.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://faceweb-004.facelink.com/edit/raw/rawimage/10/2273510.jpg?flezbwidth=140&flezbheight=160?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwi